---
target: agent
version: 1
validations:
  - name: agent-module-exists
    type: folder_check
    path: src/agent

  - name: agent-interface-defined
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the agent module defines:
      1. An Agent interface/protocol with methods: Build, Validate, GetName, GetType
      2. A BuildContext type with: Intent, Validations, ProjectRoot, OutputDir, GenerationID, DependencyNames, ProjectIntent
      3. A CLIAgent implementation that wraps any command-line tool
      4. A ClaudeAgent that extends CLIAgent through composition
      5. A CodexAgent that extends CLIAgent through composition
      6. A CreateFromProfile factory that dispatches based on provider
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/agent/**"]

  - name: agent-uses-profiles
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify that agents are constructed from AgentProfile objects:
      1. CLIAgent constructor accepts an AgentProfile (not flat config fields)
      2. ClaudeAgent constructor accepts an AgentProfile
      3. Prompt templates from the profile are used for prompt construction
      4. Tools and Skills from the profile are translated into provider-specific args
      5. CreateFromProfile dispatches based on profile.Provider
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/agent/**"]

  - name: agent-composition
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify that ClaudeAgent extends CLIAgent through composition:
      1. ClaudeAgent wraps/composes CLIAgent (not duplicates its fields)
      2. ClaudeAgent only overrides behavior where Claude-specific logic differs
      3. The claude command is hardcoded to "claude" (not configurable)
      4. Default Claude CLI args include pipe mode
      5. Profile ModelID is translated to --model flag if set
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/agent/**"]

  - name: agent-retry-logic
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify the CLIAgent implements retry logic:
      1. Retries on command failure up to profile.Retries times
      2. Waits profile.RateLimit between retries
      3. Logs each retry attempt
      4. Respects timeout from the profile
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/agent/**"]

  - name: mock-agent-exists
    type: llm_judge
    rubric: |
      Verify a mock agent exists for testing:
      1. Implements the Agent interface
      2. Records Build and Validate calls
      3. Returns configurable responses
      4. Is in test-only code (not compiled into the production binary)
    severity: error
    context_files: ["src/agent/**"]

  - name: agent-tests-pass
    type: command_check
    command: cd src && uv run pytest agent/ -v
    exit_code: 0
---

# Agent Validations

The agent system is intentc's interface to the outside world. The CLIAgent must robustly handle subprocess execution, timeout, retry, and output parsing. The ClaudeAgent should cleanly extend CLIAgent without duplication. The mock agent enables testing the rest of the system without real agent invocations.
